  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-03 15:07 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BTC net bounced above edge, SOL count softened\n\n**Task:** Re-check P1 copy intelligence after BTC sat only ~$130K above the `$15M` distribution trigger, focusing on whether net breaks down or re-stabilizes.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P1**.\n- Fresh tracker output: **BTC 6L/2S**, **ETH 2L/5S**, **SOL 4L/4S**.\n- Current top-book notional: **BTC +$15.61M net long**, **ETH -$35.68M net short**, **SOL -$10.83M net short**, **HYPE -$10.41M net short**.\n- BTC net bounced away from the immediate edge: **+$15.13M -> +$15.61M**, cushion above `$15M` improved from **~$0.13M** to **~$0.61M**.\n- BTC breadth cooled from **8L/0S** to **6L/2S**, but shorts are tiny: `beatmaker1@proton.me` **$4.2K**, `anon-0xff4c` **$623**.\n- BTC long anchors: `anon-0xfc66` **$5.63M** unchanged, `anon-0xecb6` **$4.40M** up from **$3.84M**, `anon-0x8fcc` **$4.30M** roughly flat but still below **$5M** clean-anchor size, `anon-0x57dd` **$1.10M** slightly up.\n- ETH remains high-conviction bearish: **2L/5S**, net **-$35.68M**.\n- SOL remains bearish by notional but count softened materially from **2L/6S** to **4L/4S**; net remains **-$10.83M** because large short anchors persist.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p1-btc-net-bounces-above-edge-sol-count-softens-2026-05-03-1507.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** BTC avoided the immediate distribution break. The notional bounce came mostly from `ecb6` rebuilding, while `8fcc` held around $4.3M. That stabilizes the contested-bullish read, but it still does not restore clean bullish confirmation: net is below `$17M`, and `8fcc` remains below the >$5M anchor level.\n\n**Decision:** Keep BTC label **bullish but contested / distribution watch**. Do not upgrade until BTC net reclaims **>$17M** and `8fcc` rebuilds near/above **$5M**. Distribution downgrade triggers if BTC net falls below **$15M**. Hard downgrade remains BTC net below **$10M** or `anon-0x8fcc` flips short above **$2M**. Keep ETH bearish confidence high. Downgrade SOL from max bearish to **bearish by notional, count contested**. No PM Sunday exception. No HL live trade while notional guard blocks execution.\n\n**Next:** Watch whether `ecb6` keeps rebuilding or resumes trimming. BTC must reclaim **>$17M** for clean confirmation; a drop below **$15M** flips posture defensive.\n\n## 2026-05-03 15:01 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Compression eases, BTC remains edge-watch\n\n**Task:** Refresh P4 alpha after P1 showed BTC 8L/0S but only ~$130K above the `$15M` distribution trigger, checking whether RANGE/UP becomes trend-risk or cools.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P4**.\n- Fresh alpha snapshot: `2026-05-03T15:00:06.307810+00:00`.\n- Classifier remains **`range_mean_revert_friendly`**.\n- Transition posture remains **stable**.\n- PM risk remains **low**.\n- Fast regime cooled",
